6 Requested table of characteristics
These tables summarize visit-specific characteristics overall and by child diet quality group. Continuous variables are mean (SD); categorical variables are n (%).
P-values compare Good, Moderate, and Poor diet quality groups within the same visit. Continuous variables use Kruskal-Wallis tests; categorical variables use Fisher exact tests, with chi-square fallback if Fisher exact fails.


